Description: Used in Great Shape with minimal wear, see closeup photos (minor scuffs on pick guard, small ding by jack plate) These are extremely hard to find and out of production. This 2015 Gretsch G5434T-LTD Electromatic is an iteration of the elusive White Penguin - a single-cutaway electric with an arched laminated Maple top, chambered Basswood body, and a dazzling white gloss/gold hardware combo. This is also loaded with a pair of Black Top Filter'Tron humbuckers so you can get a nice snarl out of it when you crank it, in addition to some crisp and clear tones when played quietly. This has a shorter 24.5" scale length and a comfortable 1.6875" nut width. The Maple neck is a comfortable fit and the Rosewood fingerboard has a 12" radius with 22 Medium Jumbo frets. Other cool features include an anchored Adjusto-Matic bridge and Bigsby B50G vibrato tailpiece, and enclosed vintage-style tuners. A super-slick and sweet player, this limited edition Gretsch G5434T-LTD Electromatic is a killer guitar at an unbeatable price, case is not included Single-Cutaway with White gloss finish Arched Laminated Maple top with gold Plexi pickguard and gold hardware Chambered Basswood body 24.5" scale length Maple neck Rosewood fingerboard with 12" radius, 22 Medium Jumbo frets and Pearloid Hump-Block inlays 1.6875" nut width, Synthetic Bone 2 Black Top Filter'Tron humbuckers Anchored Adjusto-Matic bridge with Bigsby B50G Vibrato tailpiece 3-way toggle switch with Master Volume, 2 Volume, and Master Tone controls Enclosed Vintage-style tuners
Title: Gretsch G5434T-LTD Electromatic Limited White Penguin Tribute Edition Rare
